58 static std::string getHostname()
59 {
60  static const int BUF_SIZE = 1024;
61  char buffer[BUF_SIZE];
62  int err = gethostname(buffer, sizeof(buffer));
63  if (err != 0)
64  return std::string();
65  else
66  {
67  buffer[BUF_SIZE - 1] = '\0';
68  return std::string(buffer);
69  }
70 }

93 void BenchmarkExecutor::initialize(const std::vector<std::string>& planning_pipeline_names)
94 {
95  planning_pipelines_.clear();
96 
97  ros::NodeHandle pnh("~");
98  for (const std::string& planning_pipeline_name : planning_pipeline_names)
99  {
100  // Initialize planning pipelines from configured child namespaces
101  ros::NodeHandle child_nh(pnh, planning_pipeline_name);
102  planning_pipeline::PlanningPipelinePtr pipeline(new planning_pipeline::PlanningPipeline(
103  planning_scene_->getRobotModel(), child_nh, "planning_plugin", "request_adapters"));
104 
105  // Verify the pipeline has successfully initialized a planner
106  if (!pipeline->getPlannerManager())
107  {
108  ROS_ERROR("Failed to initialize planning pipeline '%s'", planning_pipeline_name.c_str());
109  continue;
110  }
111 
112  // Disable visualizations and store pipeline
113  pipeline->displayComputedMotionPlans(false);
114  pipeline->checkSolutionPaths(false);
115  planning_pipelines_[planning_pipeline_name] = pipeline;
116  }
117 
118  // Error check
119  if (planning_pipelines_.empty())
120  ROS_ERROR("No planning pipelines have been loaded. Nothing to do for the benchmarking service.");
121  else
122  {
123  ROS_INFO("Available planning pipelines:");
124  for (const std::pair<const std::string, planning_pipeline::PlanningPipelinePtr>& entry : planning_pipelines_)
125  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Pipeline: " << entry.first << ", Planner: " << entry.second->getPlannerPluginName());
126  }
127 }

196 bool BenchmarkExecutor::runBenchmarks(const BenchmarkOptions& opts)
197 {
198  if (planning_pipelines_.empty())
199  {
200  ROS_ERROR("No planning pipelines configured. Did you call BenchmarkExecutor::initialize?");
201  return false;
202  }
203 
204  std::vector<BenchmarkRequest> queries;
205  moveit_msgs::PlanningScene scene_msg;
206 
207  if (initializeBenchmarks(opts, scene_msg, queries))
208  {
209  if (!queriesAndPlannersCompatible(queries, opts.getPlanningPipelineConfigurations()))
210  return false;
211 
212  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < queries.size(); ++i)
213  {
214  // Configure planning scene
215  if (scene_msg.robot_model_name != planning_scene_->getRobotModel()->getName())
216  {
217  // Clear all geometry from the scene
218  planning_scene_->getWorldNonConst()->clearObjects();
219  planning_scene_->getCurrentStateNonConst().clearAttachedBodies();
220  planning_scene_->getCurrentStateNonConst().setToDefaultValues();
221 
222  planning_scene_->processPlanningSceneWorldMsg(scene_msg.world);
223  }
224  else
225  planning_scene_->usePlanningSceneMsg(scene_msg);
226 
227  // Calling query start events
228  for (QueryStartEventFunction& query_start_fn : query_start_fns_)
229  query_start_fn(queries[i].request, planning_scene_);
230 
231  ROS_INFO("Benchmarking query '%s' (%lu of %lu)", queries[i].name.c_str(), i + 1, queries.size());
232  ros::WallTime start_time = ros::WallTime::now();
233  runBenchmark(queries[i].request, options_.getPlanningPipelineConfigurations(), options_.getNumRuns());
234  double duration = (ros::WallTime::now() - start_time).toSec();
235 
236  for (QueryCompletionEventFunction& query_end_fn : query_end_fns_)
237  query_end_fn(queries[i].request, planning_scene_);
238 
239  writeOutput(queries[i], boost::posix_time::to_iso_extended_string(start_time.toBoost()), duration);
240  }
241 
242  return true;
243  }
244  return false;
245 }
246 
247 bool BenchmarkExecutor::queriesAndPlannersCompatible(const std::vector<BenchmarkRequest>& requests,
248  const std::map<std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& /*planners*/)
249 {
250  // Make sure that the planner interfaces can service the desired queries
251  for (const std::pair<const std::string, planning_pipeline::PlanningPipelinePtr>& pipeline_entry : planning_pipelines_)
252  {
253  for (const BenchmarkRequest& request : requests)
254  {
255  if (!pipeline_entry.second->getPlannerManager()->canServiceRequest(request.request))
256  {
257  ROS_ERROR("Interface '%s' in pipeline '%s' cannot service the benchmark request '%s'",
258  pipeline_entry.second->getPlannerPluginName().c_str(), pipeline_entry.first.c_str(),
259  request.name.c_str());
260  return false;
261  }
262  }
263  }
264 
265  return true;
266 }
267 
268 bool BenchmarkExecutor::initializeBenchmarks(const BenchmarkOptions& opts, moveit_msgs::PlanningScene& scene_msg,
269  std::vector<BenchmarkRequest>& requests)
270 {
271  if (!plannerConfigurationsExist(opts.getPlanningPipelineConfigurations(), opts.getGroupName()))
272  return false;
273 
274  std::vector<StartState> start_states;
275  std::vector<PathConstraints> path_constraints;
276  std::vector<PathConstraints> goal_constraints;
277  std::vector<TrajectoryConstraints> traj_constraints;
278  std::vector<BenchmarkRequest> queries;
279 
280  if (!loadBenchmarkQueryData(opts, scene_msg, start_states, path_constraints, goal_constraints, traj_constraints,
281  queries))
282  {
283  ROS_ERROR("Failed to load benchmark query data");
284  return false;
285  }
286 
287  ROS_INFO("Benchmark loaded %lu starts, %lu goals, %lu path constraints, %lu trajectory constraints, and %lu queries",
288  start_states.size(), goal_constraints.size(), path_constraints.size(), traj_constraints.size(),
289  queries.size());
290 
291  moveit_msgs::WorkspaceParameters workspace_parameters = opts.getWorkspaceParameters();
292  // Make sure that workspace_parameters are set
293  if (workspace_parameters.min_corner.x == workspace_parameters.max_corner.x &&
294  workspace_parameters.min_corner.x == 0.0 &&
295  workspace_parameters.min_corner.y == workspace_parameters.max_corner.y &&
296  workspace_parameters.min_corner.y == 0.0 &&
297  workspace_parameters.min_corner.z == workspace_parameters.max_corner.z &&
298  workspace_parameters.min_corner.z == 0.0)
299  {
300  workspace_parameters.min_corner.x = workspace_parameters.min_corner.y = workspace_parameters.min_corner.z = -5.0;
301 
302  workspace_parameters.max_corner.x = workspace_parameters.max_corner.y = workspace_parameters.max_corner.z = 5.0;
303  }
304 
305  std::vector<double> goal_offset;
306  opts.getGoalOffsets(goal_offset);
307 
308  // Create the combinations of BenchmarkRequests
309 
310  // 1) Create requests for combinations of start states,
311  // goal constraints, and path constraints
312  for (PathConstraints& goal_constraint : goal_constraints)
313  {
314  // Common benchmark request properties
315  BenchmarkRequest brequest;
316  brequest.name = goal_constraint.name;
317  brequest.request.workspace_parameters = workspace_parameters;
318  brequest.request.goal_constraints = goal_constraint.constraints;
319  brequest.request.group_name = opts.getGroupName();
320  brequest.request.allowed_planning_time = opts.getTimeout();
321  brequest.request.num_planning_attempts = 1;
322 
323  if (brequest.request.goal_constraints.size() == 1 &&
324  brequest.request.goal_constraints[0].position_constraints.size() == 1 &&
325  brequest.request.goal_constraints[0].orientation_constraints.size() == 1 &&
326  brequest.request.goal_constraints[0].visibility_constraints.empty() &&
327  brequest.request.goal_constraints[0].joint_constraints.empty())
328  shiftConstraintsByOffset(brequest.request.goal_constraints[0], goal_offset);
329 
330  std::vector<BenchmarkRequest> request_combos;
331  createRequestCombinations(brequest, start_states, path_constraints, request_combos);
332  requests.insert(requests.end(), request_combos.begin(), request_combos.end());
333  }
334 
335  // 2) Existing queries are treated like goal constraints.
336  // Create all combos of query, start states, and path constraints
337  for (BenchmarkRequest& query : queries)
338  {
339  // Common benchmark request properties
340  BenchmarkRequest brequest;
341  brequest.name = query.name;
342  brequest.request = query.request;
343  brequest.request.group_name = opts.getGroupName();
344  brequest.request.allowed_planning_time = opts.getTimeout();
345  brequest.request.num_planning_attempts = 1;
346 
347  // Make sure that workspace_parameters are set
348  if (brequest.request.workspace_parameters.min_corner.x == brequest.request.workspace_parameters.max_corner.x &&
349  brequest.request.workspace_parameters.min_corner.x == 0.0 &&
350  brequest.request.workspace_parameters.min_corner.y == brequest.request.workspace_parameters.max_corner.y &&
351  brequest.request.workspace_parameters.min_corner.y == 0.0 &&
352  brequest.request.workspace_parameters.min_corner.z == brequest.request.workspace_parameters.max_corner.z &&
353  brequest.request.workspace_parameters.min_corner.z == 0.0)
354  {
355  // ROS_WARN("Workspace parameters are not set for request %s. Setting defaults", queries[i].name.c_str());
356  brequest.request.workspace_parameters = workspace_parameters;
357  }
358 
359  // Create all combinations of start states and path constraints
360  std::vector<BenchmarkRequest> request_combos;
361  createRequestCombinations(brequest, start_states, path_constraints, request_combos);
362  requests.insert(requests.end(), request_combos.begin(), request_combos.end());
363  }
364 
365  // 3) Trajectory constraints are also treated like goal constraints
366  for (TrajectoryConstraints& traj_constraint : traj_constraints)
367  {
368  // Common benchmark request properties
369  BenchmarkRequest brequest;
370  brequest.name = traj_constraint.name;
371  brequest.request.trajectory_constraints = traj_constraint.constraints;
372  brequest.request.group_name = opts.getGroupName();
373  brequest.request.allowed_planning_time = opts.getTimeout();
374  brequest.request.num_planning_attempts = 1;
375 
376  if (brequest.request.trajectory_constraints.constraints.size() == 1 &&
377  brequest.request.trajectory_constraints.constraints[0].position_constraints.size() == 1 &&
378  brequest.request.trajectory_constraints.constraints[0].orientation_constraints.size() == 1 &&
379  brequest.request.trajectory_constraints.constraints[0].visibility_constraints.empty() &&
380  brequest.request.trajectory_constraints.constraints[0].joint_constraints.empty())
381  shiftConstraintsByOffset(brequest.request.trajectory_constraints.constraints[0], goal_offset);
382 
383  std::vector<BenchmarkRequest> request_combos;
384  std::vector<PathConstraints> no_path_constraints;
385  createRequestCombinations(brequest, start_states, no_path_constraints, request_combos);
386  requests.insert(requests.end(), request_combos.begin(), request_combos.end());
387  }
388 
389  options_ = opts;
390  return true;
391 }
392 
393 bool BenchmarkExecutor::loadBenchmarkQueryData(const BenchmarkOptions& opts, moveit_msgs::PlanningScene& scene_msg,
394  std::vector<StartState>& start_states,
395  std::vector<PathConstraints>& path_constraints,
396  std::vector<PathConstraints>& goal_constraints,
397  std::vector<TrajectoryConstraints>& traj_constraints,
398  std::vector<BenchmarkRequest>& queries)
399 {
400  try
401  {
402  warehouse_ros::DatabaseConnection::Ptr warehouse_connection = dbloader.loadDatabase();
403  warehouse_connection->setParams(opts.getHostName(), opts.getPort(), 20);
404  if (warehouse_connection->connect())
405  {
406  pss_ = new moveit_warehouse::PlanningSceneStorage(warehouse_connection);
407  psws_ = new moveit_warehouse::PlanningSceneWorldStorage(warehouse_connection);
408  rs_ = new moveit_warehouse::RobotStateStorage(warehouse_connection);
409  cs_ = new moveit_warehouse::ConstraintsStorage(warehouse_connection);
410  tcs_ = new moveit_warehouse::TrajectoryConstraintsStorage(warehouse_connection);
411  }
412  else
413  {
414  ROS_ERROR("Failed to connect to DB");
415  return false;
416  }
417  }
418  catch (std::exception& e)
419  {
420  ROS_ERROR("Failed to initialize benchmark server: '%s'", e.what());
421  return false;
422  }
423 
424  return loadPlanningScene(opts.getSceneName(), scene_msg) && loadStates(opts.getStartStateRegex(), start_states) &&
425  loadPathConstraints(opts.getGoalConstraintRegex(), goal_constraints) &&
426  loadPathConstraints(opts.getPathConstraintRegex(), path_constraints) &&
427  loadTrajectoryConstraints(opts.getTrajectoryConstraintRegex(), traj_constraints) &&
428  loadQueries(opts.getQueryRegex(), opts.getSceneName(), queries);
429 }

431 void BenchmarkExecutor::shiftConstraintsByOffset(moveit_msgs::Constraints& constraints,
432  const std::vector<double>& offset)
433 {
434  Eigen::Isometry3d offset_tf(Eigen::AngleAxis<double>(offset[3], Eigen::Vector3d::UnitX()) *
435  Eigen::AngleAxis<double>(offset[4], Eigen::Vector3d::UnitY()) *
436  Eigen::AngleAxis<double>(offset[5], Eigen::Vector3d::UnitZ()));
437  offset_tf.translation() = Eigen::Vector3d(offset[0], offset[1], offset[2]);
438 
439  geometry_msgs::Pose constraint_pose_msg;
440  constraint_pose_msg.position = constraints.position_constraints[0].constraint_region.primitive_poses[0].position;
441  constraint_pose_msg.orientation = constraints.orientation_constraints[0].orientation;
442  Eigen::Isometry3d constraint_pose;
443  tf2::fromMsg(constraint_pose_msg, constraint_pose);
444 
445  Eigen::Isometry3d new_pose = constraint_pose * offset_tf;
446  geometry_msgs::Pose new_pose_msg;
447  new_pose_msg = tf2::toMsg(new_pose);
448 
449  constraints.position_constraints[0].constraint_region.primitive_poses[0].position = new_pose_msg.position;
450  constraints.orientation_constraints[0].orientation = new_pose_msg.orientation;
451 }

453 void BenchmarkExecutor::createRequestCombinations(const BenchmarkRequest& brequest,
454  const std::vector<StartState>& start_states,
455  const std::vector<PathConstraints>& path_constraints,
456  std::vector<BenchmarkRequest>& requests)
457 {
458  // Use default start state
459  if (start_states.empty())
460  {
461  // Adding path constraints
462  for (const PathConstraints& path_constraint : path_constraints)
463  {
464  BenchmarkRequest new_brequest = brequest;
465  new_brequest.request.path_constraints = path_constraint.constraints[0];
466  new_brequest.name = brequest.name + "_" + path_constraint.name;
467  requests.push_back(new_brequest);
468  }
469 
470  if (path_constraints.empty())
471  requests.push_back(brequest);
472  }
473  else // Create a request for each start state specified
474  {
475  for (const StartState& start_state : start_states)
476  {
477  // Skip start states that have the same name as the goal
478  if (start_state.name == brequest.name)
479  continue;
480 
481  BenchmarkRequest new_brequest = brequest;
482  new_brequest.request.start_state = start_state.state;
483 
484  // Duplicate the request for each of the path constraints
485  for (const PathConstraints& path_constraint : path_constraints)
486  {
487  new_brequest.request.path_constraints = path_constraint.constraints[0];
488  new_brequest.name = start_state.name + "_" + new_brequest.name + "_" + path_constraint.name;
489  requests.push_back(new_brequest);
490  }
491 
492  if (path_constraints.empty())
493  {
494  new_brequest.name = start_state.name + "_" + brequest.name;
495  requests.push_back(new_brequest);
496  }
497  }
498  }
499 }

501 bool BenchmarkExecutor::plannerConfigurationsExist(
502  const std::map<std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& pipeline_configurations, const std::string& group_name)
503 {
504  // Make sure planner plugins exist
505  for (const std::pair<const std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& pipeline_config_entry : pipeline_configurations)
506  {
507  bool pipeline_exists = false;
508  for (const std::pair<const std::string, planning_pipeline::PlanningPipelinePtr>& pipeline_entry :
509  planning_pipelines_)
510  {
511  pipeline_exists = pipeline_entry.first == pipeline_config_entry.first;
512  if (pipeline_exists)
513  break;
514  }
515 
516  if (!pipeline_exists)
517  {
518  ROS_ERROR("Planning pipeline '%s' does NOT exist", pipeline_config_entry.first.c_str());
519  return false;
520  }
521  }
522 
523  // Make sure planners exist within those pipelines
524  for (const std::pair<const std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& entry : pipeline_configurations)
525  {
526  planning_interface::PlannerManagerPtr pm = planning_pipelines_[entry.first]->getPlannerManager();
527  const planning_interface::PlannerConfigurationMap& config_map = pm->getPlannerConfigurations();
528 
529  // if the planner is chomp or stomp skip this function and return true for checking planner configurations for the
530  // planning group otherwise an error occurs, because for OMPL a specific planning algorithm needs to be defined for
531  // a planning group, whereas with STOMP and CHOMP this is not necessary
532  if (pm->getDescription().compare("stomp") || pm->getDescription().compare("chomp"))
533  continue;
534 
535  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < entry.second.size(); ++i)
536  {
537  bool planner_exists = false;
538  for (const std::pair<const std::string, planning_interface::PlannerConfigurationSettings>& config_entry :
539  config_map)
540  {
541  std::string planner_name = group_name + "[" + entry.second[i] + "]";
542  planner_exists = (config_entry.second.group == group_name && config_entry.second.name == planner_name);
543  }
544 
545  if (!planner_exists)
546  {
547  ROS_ERROR("Planner '%s' does NOT exist for group '%s' in pipeline '%s'", entry.second[i].c_str(),
548  group_name.c_str(), entry.first.c_str());
549  std::cout << "There are " << config_map.size() << " planner entries: " << std::endl;
550  for (const auto& config_map_entry : config_map)
551  std::cout << config_map_entry.second.name << std::endl;
552  return false;
553  }
554  }
555  }
556 
557  return true;
558 }
559 
560 bool BenchmarkExecutor::loadPlanningScene(const std::string& scene_name, moveit_msgs::PlanningScene& scene_msg)
561 {
562  bool ok = false;
563  try
564  {
565  if (pss_->hasPlanningScene(scene_name)) // whole planning scene
566  {
567  moveit_warehouse::PlanningSceneWithMetadata pswm;
568  ok = pss_->getPlanningScene(pswm, scene_name);
569  scene_msg = static_cast<moveit_msgs::PlanningScene>(*pswm);
570 
571  if (!ok)
572  ROS_ERROR("Failed to load planning scene '%s'", scene_name.c_str());
573  }
574  else if (psws_->hasPlanningSceneWorld(scene_name)) // Just the world (no robot)
575  {
576  moveit_warehouse::PlanningSceneWorldWithMetadata pswwm;
577  ok = psws_->getPlanningSceneWorld(pswwm, scene_name);
578  scene_msg.world = static_cast<moveit_msgs::PlanningSceneWorld>(*pswwm);
579  scene_msg.robot_model_name =
580  "NO ROBOT INFORMATION. ONLY WORLD GEOMETRY"; // this will be fixed when running benchmark
581 
582  if (!ok)
583  ROS_ERROR("Failed to load planning scene '%s'", scene_name.c_str());
584  }
585  else
586  ROS_ERROR("Failed to find planning scene '%s'", scene_name.c_str());
587  }
588  catch (std::exception& ex)
589  {
590  ROS_ERROR("Error loading planning scene: %s", ex.what());
591  }
592  ROS_INFO("Loaded planning scene successfully");
593  return ok;
594 }

596 bool BenchmarkExecutor::loadQueries(const std::string& regex, const std::string& scene_name,
597  std::vector<BenchmarkRequest>& queries)
598 {
599  if (regex.empty())
600  return true;
601 
602  std::vector<std::string> query_names;
603  try
604  {

606  }
607  catch (std::exception& ex)

610  return false;
611  }
612 
613  if (query_names.empty())
614  {
615  ROS_ERROR("Scene '%s' has no associated queries", scene_name.c_str());
616  return false;
617  }
618 
619  for (const std::string& query_name : query_names)
620  {
621  moveit_warehouse::MotionPlanRequestWithMetadata planning_query;
622  try
623  {

625  }
626  catch (std::exception& ex)
627  {
628  ROS_ERROR("Error loading motion planning query '%s': %s", query_name.c_str(), ex.what());
629  continue;
630  }
631 
632  BenchmarkRequest query;
633  query.name = query_name;
634  query.request = static_cast<moveit_msgs::MotionPlanRequest>(*planning_query);
635  queries.push_back(query);
636  }
637  ROS_INFO("Loaded queries successfully");
638  return true;

750 void BenchmarkExecutor::runBenchmark(moveit_msgs::MotionPlanRequest request,
751  const std::map<std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& pipeline_map, int runs)
752 {
753  benchmark_data_.clear();
754 
755  unsigned int num_planners = 0;
756  for (const std::pair<const std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& pipeline_entry : pipeline_map)
757  num_planners += pipeline_entry.second.size();
758 
759  boost::progress_display progress(num_planners * runs, std::cout);
760 
761  // Iterate through all planning pipelines
762  for (const std::pair<const std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& pipeline_entry : pipeline_map)
763  {
764  planning_pipeline::PlanningPipelinePtr planning_pipeline = planning_pipelines_[pipeline_entry.first];
765  // Use the planning context if the pipeline only contains the planner plugin
766  bool use_planning_context = planning_pipeline->getAdapterPluginNames().empty();
767  // Iterate through all planners configured for the pipeline
768  for (const std::string& planner_id : pipeline_entry.second)
769  {
770  // This container stores all of the benchmark data for this planner
771  PlannerBenchmarkData planner_data(runs);
772  // This vector stores all motion plan results for further evaluation
773  std::vector<planning_interface::MotionPlanDetailedResponse> responses(runs);
774  std::vector<bool> solved(runs);
775 
776  request.planner_id = planner_id;
777 
778  // Planner start events
779  for (PlannerStartEventFunction& planner_start_fn : planner_start_fns_)
780  planner_start_fn(request, planner_data);
781 
782  planning_interface::PlanningContextPtr planning_context;
783  if (use_planning_context)
784  planning_context = planning_pipeline->getPlannerManager()->getPlanningContext(planning_scene_, request);
785 
786  // Iterate runs
787  for (int j = 0; j < runs; ++j)
788  {
789  // Pre-run events
790  for (PreRunEventFunction& pre_event_fn : pre_event_fns_)
791  pre_event_fn(request);
792 
793  // Solve problem
794  ros::WallTime start = ros::WallTime::now();
795  if (use_planning_context)
796  {
797  solved[j] = planning_context->solve(responses[j]);
798  }
799  else
800  {
801  // The planning pipeline does not support MotionPlanDetailedResponse
802  planning_interface::MotionPlanResponse response;
803  solved[j] = planning_pipeline->generatePlan(planning_scene_, request, response);
804  responses[j].error_code_ = response.error_code_;
805  if (response.trajectory_)
806  {
807  responses[j].description_.push_back("plan");
808  responses[j].trajectory_.push_back(response.trajectory_);
809  responses[j].processing_time_.push_back(response.planning_time_);
810  }
811  }
812  double total_time = (ros::WallTime::now() - start).toSec();
813 
814  // Collect data
815  start = ros::WallTime::now();
816 
817  // Post-run events
818  for (PostRunEventFunction& post_event_fn : post_event_fns_)
819  post_event_fn(request, responses[j], planner_data[j]);
820  collectMetrics(planner_data[j], responses[j], solved[j], total_time);
821  double metrics_time = (ros::WallTime::now() - start).toSec();
822  ROS_DEBUG("Spent %lf seconds collecting metrics", metrics_time);
823 
824  ++progress;
825  }
826 
827  computeAveragePathSimilarities(planner_data, responses, solved);
828 
829  // Planner completion events
830  for (PlannerCompletionEventFunction& planner_completion_fn : planner_completion_fns_)
831  planner_completion_fn(request, planner_data);
832 
833  benchmark_data_.push_back(planner_data);
834  }
835  }
836 }
837 
838 void BenchmarkExecutor::collectMetrics(PlannerRunData& metrics,
839  const planning_interface::MotionPlanDetailedResponse& mp_res, bool solved,
840  double total_time)
841 {
842  metrics["time REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(total_time);
843  metrics["solved BOOLEAN"] = boost::lexical_cast<std::string>(solved);
844 
845  if (solved)
846  {
847  // Analyzing the trajectory(ies) geometrically
848  double traj_len = 0.0; // trajectory length
849  double clearance = 0.0; // trajectory clearance (average)
850  double smoothness = 0.0; // trajectory smoothness (average)
851  bool correct = true; // entire trajectory collision free and in bounds
852 
853  double process_time = total_time;
854  for (std::size_t j = 0; j < mp_res.trajectory_.size(); ++j)
855  {
856  correct = true;
857  traj_len = 0.0;
858  clearance = 0.0;
859  smoothness = 0.0;
860  const robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory& p = *mp_res.trajectory_[j];
861 
862  // compute path length
863  for (std::size_t k = 1; k < p.getWayPointCount(); ++k)
864  traj_len += p.getWayPoint(k - 1).distance(p.getWayPoint(k));
865 
866  // compute correctness and clearance
867  collision_detection::CollisionRequest req;
868  for (std::size_t k = 0; k < p.getWayPointCount(); ++k)
869  {
870  collision_detection::CollisionResult res;
871  planning_scene_->checkCollisionUnpadded(req, res, p.getWayPoint(k));
872  if (res.collision)
873  correct = false;
874  if (!p.getWayPoint(k).satisfiesBounds())
875  correct = false;
876  double d = planning_scene_->distanceToCollisionUnpadded(p.getWayPoint(k));
877  if (d > 0.0) // in case of collision, distance is negative
878  clearance += d;
879  }
880  clearance /= (double)p.getWayPointCount();
881 
882  // compute smoothness
883  if (p.getWayPointCount() > 2)
884  {
885  double a = p.getWayPoint(0).distance(p.getWayPoint(1));
886  for (std::size_t k = 2; k < p.getWayPointCount(); ++k)
887  {
888  // view the path as a sequence of segments, and look at the triangles it forms:
889  // s1
890  // /\ s4
891  // a / \ b |
892  // / \ |
893  // /......\_______|
894  // s0 c s2 s3
895  //
896 
897  // use Pythagoras generalized theorem to find the cos of the angle between segments a and b
898  double b = p.getWayPoint(k - 1).distance(p.getWayPoint(k));
899  double cdist = p.getWayPoint(k - 2).distance(p.getWayPoint(k));
900  double acos_value = (a * a + b * b - cdist * cdist) / (2.0 * a * b);
901  if (acos_value > -1.0 && acos_value < 1.0)
902  {
903  // the smoothness is actually the outside angle of the one we compute
904  double angle = (boost::math::constants::pi<double>() - acos(acos_value));
905 
906  // and we normalize by the length of the segments
907  double u = 2.0 * angle;
908  smoothness += u * u;
909  }
910  a = b;
911  }
912  smoothness /= (double)p.getWayPointCount();
913  }
914  metrics["path_" + mp_res.description_[j] + "_correct BOOLEAN"] = boost::lexical_cast<std::string>(correct);
915  metrics["path_" + mp_res.description_[j] + "_length REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(traj_len);
916  metrics["path_" + mp_res.description_[j] + "_clearance REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(clearance);
917  metrics["path_" + mp_res.description_[j] + "_smoothness REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(smoothness);
918  metrics["path_" + mp_res.description_[j] + "_time REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(mp_res.processing_time_[j]);
919 
920  if (j == mp_res.trajectory_.size() - 1)
921  {
922  metrics["final_path_correct BOOLEAN"] = boost::lexical_cast<std::string>(correct);
923  metrics["final_path_length REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(traj_len);
924  metrics["final_path_clearance REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(clearance);
925  metrics["final_path_smoothness REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(smoothness);
926  metrics["final_path_time REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(mp_res.processing_time_[j]);
927  }
928  process_time -= mp_res.processing_time_[j];
929  }
930  if (process_time <= 0.0)
931  process_time = 0.0;
932  metrics["process_time REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(process_time);
933  }
934 }
935 
936 void BenchmarkExecutor::computeAveragePathSimilarities(
937  PlannerBenchmarkData& planner_data, const std::vector<planning_interface::MotionPlanDetailedResponse>& responses,
938  const std::vector<bool>& solved)
939 {
940  ROS_INFO("Computing result path similarity");
941  const size_t result_count = planner_data.size();
942  size_t unsolved = std::count_if(solved.begin(), solved.end(), [](bool s) { return !s; });
943  std::vector<double> average_distances(responses.size());
944  for (size_t first_traj_i = 0; first_traj_i < result_count; ++first_traj_i)
945  {
946  // If trajectory was not solved there is no valid average distance so it's set to max double only
947  if (!solved[first_traj_i])
948  {
949  average_distances[first_traj_i] = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
950  continue;
951  }
952  // Iterate all result trajectories that haven't been compared yet
953  for (size_t second_traj_i = first_traj_i + 1; second_traj_i < result_count; ++second_traj_i)
954  {
955  // Ignore if other result has not been solved
956  if (!solved[second_traj_i])
957  continue;
958 
959  // Get final trajectories
960  const robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory& traj_first = *responses[first_traj_i].trajectory_.back();
961  const robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory& traj_second = *responses[second_traj_i].trajectory_.back();
962 
963  // Compute trajectory distance
964  double trajectory_distance;
965  if (!computeTrajectoryDistance(traj_first, traj_second, trajectory_distance))
966  continue;
967 
968  // Add average distance to counters of both trajectories
969  average_distances[first_traj_i] += trajectory_distance;
970  average_distances[second_traj_i] += trajectory_distance;
971  }
972  // Normalize average distance by number of actual comparisons
973  average_distances[first_traj_i] /= result_count - unsolved - 1;
974  }
975 
976  // Store results in planner_data
977  for (size_t i = 0; i < result_count; ++i)
978  planner_data[i]["average_waypoint_distance REAL"] = moveit::core::toString(average_distances[i]);
979 }
980 
981 bool BenchmarkExecutor::computeTrajectoryDistance(const robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory& traj_first,
982  const robot_trajectory::RobotTrajectory& traj_second,
983  double& result_distance)
984 {
985  // Abort if trajectories are empty
986  if (traj_first.empty() || traj_second.empty())
987  return false;
988 
989  // Waypoint counter
990  size_t pos_first = 0;
991  size_t pos_second = 0;
992  const size_t max_pos_first = traj_first.getWayPointCount() - 1;
993  const size_t max_pos_second = traj_second.getWayPointCount() - 1;
994 
995  // Compute total distance between pairwise waypoints of both trajectories.
996  // The selection of waypoint pairs is based on what steps results in the minimal distance between the next pair of
997  // waypoints. We first check what steps are still possible or if we reached the end of the trajectories. Then we
998  // compute the pairwise waypoint distances of the pairs from increasing both, the first, or the second trajectory.
999  // Finally we select the pair that results in the minimal distance, summarize the total distance and iterate
1000  // accordingly. After that we compute the average trajectory distance by normalizing over the number of steps.
1001  double total_distance = 0;
1002  size_t steps = 0;
1003  double current_distance = traj_first.getWayPoint(pos_first).distance(traj_second.getWayPoint(pos_second));
1004  while (true)
1005  {
1006  // Keep track of total distance and number of comparisons
1007  total_distance += current_distance;
1008  ++steps;
1009  if (pos_first == max_pos_first && pos_second == max_pos_second) // end reached
1010  break;
1011 
1012  // Determine what steps are still possible
1013  bool can_up_first = pos_first < max_pos_first;
1014  bool can_up_second = pos_second < max_pos_second;
1015  bool can_up_both = can_up_first && can_up_second;
1016 
1017  // Compute pair-wise waypoint distances (increasing both, first, or second trajectories).
1018  double up_both = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
1019  double up_first = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
1020  double up_second = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
1021  if (can_up_both)
1022  up_both = traj_first.getWayPoint(pos_first + 1).distance(traj_second.getWayPoint(pos_second + 1));
1023  if (can_up_first)
1024  up_first = traj_first.getWayPoint(pos_first + 1).distance(traj_second.getWayPoint(pos_second));
1025  if (can_up_second)
1026  up_second = traj_first.getWayPoint(pos_first).distance(traj_second.getWayPoint(pos_second + 1));
1027 
1028  // Select actual step, store new distance value and iterate trajectory positions
1029  if (can_up_both && up_both < up_first && up_both < up_second)
1030  {
1031  ++pos_first;
1032  ++pos_second;
1033  current_distance = up_both;
1034  }
1035  else if ((can_up_first && up_first < up_second) || !can_up_second)
1036  {
1037  ++pos_first;
1038  current_distance = up_first;
1039  }
1040  else if (can_up_second)
1041  {
1042  ++pos_second;
1043  current_distance = up_second;
1044  }
1045  }
1046  // Normalize trajectory distance by number of comparison steps
1047  result_distance = total_distance / static_cast<double>(steps);
1048  return true;
1049 }

1051 void BenchmarkExecutor::writeOutput(const BenchmarkRequest& brequest, const std::string& start_time,
1052  double benchmark_duration)
1053 {
1054  const std::map<std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& pipelines = options_.getPlanningPipelineConfigurations();
1055 
1056  size_t num_planners = 0;
1057  for (const std::pair<const std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& pipeline : pipelines)
1058  num_planners += pipeline.second.size();
1059 
1060  std::string hostname = getHostname();
1061  if (hostname.empty())
1062  hostname = "UNKNOWN";
1063 
1064  std::string filename = options_.getOutputDirectory();
1065  if (!filename.empty() && filename[filename.size() - 1] != '/')
1066  filename.append("/");
1067 
1068  // Ensure directories exist
1069  boost::filesystem::create_directories(filename);
1070 
1071  filename += (options_.getBenchmarkName().empty() ? "" : options_.getBenchmarkName() + "_") + brequest.name + "_" +
1072  getHostname() + "_" + start_time + ".log";
1073  std::ofstream out(filename.c_str());
1074  if (!out)
1075  {
1076  ROS_ERROR("Failed to open '%s' for benchmark output", filename.c_str());
1077  return;
1078  }
1079 
1080  out << "MoveIt version " << MOVEIT_VERSION << std::endl;
1081  out << "Experiment " << brequest.name << std::endl;
1082  out << "Running on " << hostname << std::endl;
1083  out << "Starting at " << start_time << std::endl;
1084 
1085  // Experiment setup
1086  moveit_msgs::PlanningScene scene_msg;
1087  planning_scene_->getPlanningSceneMsg(scene_msg);
1088  out << "<<<|" << std::endl;
1089  out << "Motion plan request:" << std::endl << brequest.request << std::endl;
1090  out << "Planning scene: " << std::endl << scene_msg << std::endl << "|>>>" << std::endl;
1091 
1092  // Not writing optional cpu information
1093 
1094  // The real random seed is unknown. Writing a fake value
1095  out << "0 is the random seed" << std::endl;
1096  out << brequest.request.allowed_planning_time << " seconds per run" << std::endl;
1097  // There is no memory cap
1098  out << "-1 MB per run" << std::endl;
1099  out << options_.getNumRuns() << " runs per planner" << std::endl;
1100  out << benchmark_duration << " seconds spent to collect the data" << std::endl;
1101 
1102  // No enum types
1103  out << "0 enum types" << std::endl;
1104 
1105  out << num_planners << " planners" << std::endl;
1106 
1107  size_t run_id = 0;
1108  for (const std::pair<const std::string, std::vector<std::string>>& pipeline : pipelines)
1109  {
1110  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < pipeline.second.size(); ++i, ++run_id)
1111  {
1112  // Write the name of the planner and the used pipeline
1113  out << pipeline.second[i] << " (" << pipeline.first << ")" << std::endl;
1114 
1115  // in general, we could have properties specific for a planner;
1116  // right now, we do not include such properties
1117  out << "0 common properties" << std::endl;
1118 
1119  // Create a list of the benchmark properties for this planner
1120  std::set<std::string> properties_set;
1121  for (PlannerRunData& planner_run_data : benchmark_data_[run_id]) // each run of this planner
1122  for (PlannerRunData::const_iterator pit = planner_run_data.begin(); pit != planner_run_data.end();
1123  ++pit) // each benchmark property of the given run
1124  properties_set.insert(pit->first);
1125 
1126  // Writing property list
1127  out << properties_set.size() << " properties for each run" << std::endl;
1128  for (const std::string& property : properties_set)
1129  out << property << std::endl;
1130 
1131  // Number of runs
1132  out << benchmark_data_[run_id].size() << " runs" << std::endl;
1133 
1134  // And the benchmark properties
1135  for (PlannerRunData& planner_run_data : benchmark_data_[run_id]) // each run of this planner
1136  {
1137  // Write out properties in the order we listed them above
1138  for (const std::string& property : properties_set)
1139  {
1140  // Make sure this run has this property
1141  PlannerRunData::const_iterator runit = planner_run_data.find(property);
1142  if (runit != planner_run_data.end())
1143  out << runit->second;
1144  out << "; ";
1145  }
1146  out << std::endl; // end of the run
1147  }
1148  out << "." << std::endl; // end the planner
1149  }
1150  }
1151 
1152  out.close();
1153  ROS_INFO("Benchmark results saved to '%s'", filename.c_str());
1154 }
